description.nl: Qualification(s) or periods of study required for access to the programme.

Details of access to further academic and/or professional studies the qualification provides, especially to specific qualifications, or levels of study, e.g.: access to Doctoral studies in the country or institution.
The uppermost administrative unit for the address, almost always a country.
The discipline or subject area of a course.
A mark indicating a degree of accomplishment for a particular course.
Main language in which the course was taught.
The grade point average of the course results, i.e. grades weighted based on the number of credits.
The language in which the Tertiary Education Evidence is issued.
The different languages in which the programme was given.
Indication of the level of distinction with which an academic degree has been earned, e.g. First Class Honors Degree, Summa Cum Laude, Merit, Avec Distinction, Avec mention, etc.
The main disciplines or subject areas of a qualification.
The way the programme was undertaken, e.g. full-time, part-time, intermittent/sandwich, e-learning, distance, etc.
A mark indicating a degree of accomplishment.
The chromosomal state, and reproductive organs and structures of a Person that allows them to be distinguished as female or male.
An indicator of the status of the course and the obtained grade, e.g. pass, fail, in-progress, unknown.
